name: Richard Foster
text:
Sorry, this is a rather long comment. First, on a positive note. The store looks great and it's great to have a good hardware store so close. Also, the personnel were knowledgeable which usually is why I prefer stores like this over Big box retailers.

So I've had a day to consider my experience at this store. I was excited to have a reason to go to the new Ace store not too far from me. It didn't go well. And for perspective, I almost never strongly complain. But, to start, I'm exceptionally busy and need a place that is easy for transactions and returns. So, being busy, I went to the shed and found out I didn't have the key for the pad lock. I ran to Ace and picked up a small bolt cutter. Coming home, I tried twice on the lock and realized it was too small.

Returning to the store, I tried to return the item within 30 minutes of purchase (with receipt) to buy a large Bolt cutter. This is when I found out about the 'no return' for used items policy. OK, I can accept that. I won't be able to shop there. But I accept that. The problem? From my perspective, the owner was rude. 'No, we won't take that back. It's used' he said. IMO, 'I'm sorry, we're an independent franchise and we can't afford to take back used items' would have been a much better response.

One other story. Last year, I bought a push mower at Lowes. I tried it and it wasn't sufficient. I took it back and got a more powerful mower. They took it back no questions asked. Had I bought it at this Ace? Nope, no returns on used items. I could be wrong but I also assume you can't  bring back defectives items (it's under warranty so deal with the manufacturer?) I could be wrong there. But again, with all that's on my plate, I need easy returns. With all that said, I wish this store well. We need you here.

name: Debbie Reeves
text: As of this writing (late August 2021), the store is a brand new store. They just opened a few weeks ago. Being a new store, everything is squeaky clean and everything is on place. The ladies there were super nice and helpful. I would go back again because they are convenient to go to and have good selections of hardware.

name: NameHidden ForPrivacy
text:
Bought a brand new Stihl chainsaw from this establishment.   After 20 minutes of running the saw broke and needed a new head.

First Stihl gave me a hard time about the saw, made me take pictures of an obviously brand new saw and after a lot of hull-a-ba-loo agreed to fix the saw.

Then they had Electrical Outlet fix it.  It took Electrical Outlet six months to fix the saw.

Went back into Electrical Outlet today (a year later after the saw fiasco) and put $300 dollars worth of material into my buggy.

I went to get a log chain and requested help from the owner, a Mr. Alexander.

He helped me get the chain and I requested help obtaining hooks to put on the end of the chain.

I had some reservations about the eye hooks, such as would they be as sturdy as the chain itself.  What type was better, etc.

During this question session three men came up to us and interrupted our conversation.  Mr. Alexander then just left me standing there with a couple of different hooks in my hand and walked away to discuss college football with what were apparently his friends.

So, I shopped a bit more, patiently waited at the front desk while these four people gabbed about college football.

When Mr. Alexander finally decided to check me out I indicated I was not happy with his leaving me standing there.

While explaining this I did not raise my voice or act rudely, I simply told him I wasn't happy with the service level provided.

It was at this time that Mr. Alexander decided to go ballistic on me.

I got a good reaming out by him.  For good measure he also tossed in a few choice four letter words.

I told him that I was having a difficult time being calm with him.

To that he pointed at the door and told me to get out.

I then told him about my chain saw experience and that I had refrained from criticizing the store about the poor service because one of his young employees had been very nice to me during a weather emergency we had April 27th, 2011.

Once again I got told where the door was and to use it.

So, I proceeded to do so.

As I was opening the door he shouted at me "You must be another one of those Terry's".  I promptly told him who I was and spelled my name out for him.

I try to support local businesses, but he effectively sent me next door to Tractor Supply (where I got everything I came to town for anyway).  Guess it will be Tractor Supply or Lowes in the big city from here on out.

Good luck with your attitude Mr. Alexander.  It will take your business straight down!

name: Jade Bertovic
text: My husband and I were in desperate need of replacement windows for our new (to us) home. We had been putting off the process and finally bit the bullet when a friend recommended Holcombe Doors and Windows. Before we replaced our windows, our rooms were stifling hot in the summer and freezing in the winter even with the A/C or heat running. Which also meant our power bills were much higher than need be. As soon as we replaced our old windows with new, efficient windows from Holcombe Doors and Windows, we could tell a HUGE difference not only in the appearance, but our rooms were no longer hot in the summer or cold in the winter! Holcombe did an outstanding job helping us decide what windows were right for our home and completing the job. Their customer service and install team were professional, friendly and helpful. We are beyond pleased with the job Holcombe did for us, and will definitely be using them again!

name: Lee Mears
text:
Have always gotten good service. Good selection of home improvement needs. Nice to have a hometown hardware store and not have to drive 1/2 hour to one of the big box stores.
I do find it sad that none of these 1 star reviews that I have seen are written by people who live around here. It's absolutely amazing that folks from other parts of the country know so much about the quality of the product and service without ever being remotely close to the store.
All of these people complaining about the store and the staff being prejudiced have not met the owners or set foot in the store, but rather, they are basing their opinions on what they have heard on a podcast from NPR in which the reporter made some major assumptions and distortions to create a more dramatic story, and paint someone as the bad guy.
Wait a second.... All these folks that are jumping to their conclusions from an edited and arranged story specifically designed to envoke that response, and not finding out the facts of the situation or meeting the people involved, are displaying a reprehensible behavior. What would it be called???
Hmmm....maybe prejudice???

name: Sammi Reynolds
text: So I recently financed a Chevy blazer from family building supply in Blountsville Alabama at first it wasn't to bad the car was ran down but still usable. Now when I got it they told me that if I needed repairs I could take it back to them and they would only charge me for the price of the parts. I was thinking it was a good deal. But however a couple weeks ago it needed wheel bearings wheel assemblies and a whole bunch more so I took it to them and the replaced it all. Now last weekend I was going about 40, mabe, on a the road to see my kids. The roads weren't wet yet it was b4 the rain. However, as I went around a slight curve something happened I can't explain but the car turned completely to the left and hit the side bank and flipped 3 times. The people who were outside and saw it all said it looked like a full mechanical issue. Now when I told the insurance company and they asked family building supplies they said they never worked on the car. I had called and asked them for a detailed receipt of wat they did they said no it had nothing to do with the accident. Now I am 3 months pregnant and somehow some1 was looking out for me and the baby cause I had no serious injuries and the baby was fine. But besides the point they r not any1 I would ever recommend any1 to go to ever!!!

name: david loeser
text:
I normally do not do reviews but this place does not practice good business. They are not for the customer but only want to make a sell. My wife had a list of exactly what was needed from the person who was installing the flooring in our house and she showed the list to the people who work there. They showed my wife flooring and she picked the color she likes. Not knowing the type of floor was wrong. Remember these are the “experts”. We unloaded all the floor at the house the next morning the person installing asked why they gave us the wrong stuff. We ended up having to return the floor which we would have purchased the right floor from them but they charged us a 20% restocking fee because they sold us the wrong floor. Knowing what was asked for and needed as my wife showed pictures of the subfloor.

Nonetheless they lost our business and stole 20% because they should have fit that bill due to their lack of of professionalism and customer service.

If you want the cheapest price maybe they are the place to go, who knows. But if you want customer service and want to be sure you are getting the best product for your needs this is definitely not the place to go.

resp.text: Yes they did give us a list of materials they needed. On that list were the items that they needed for a remodel and there was a quantity of flooring that they needed not a specific floor but just a quantity. We asked her what type of floor she was looking for so we helped her get a waterproof floor that she asked for. She had over 100 options to choose, yes we have a great variety at great low prices. Theirs was a 5mm/20mil wear layer at only $1.49 Sf by the way. She even took a sample of the entire piece. When they came to return the floor the installer came with her and he said that he seen the piece when they brought it to their home, he said that he seen the sample  when he was at the store. Why he did not mention he could not install that type of floor in that house we do not know (this was before the purchase was made). We gave her the floor she chose not a wrong one. She also read and signed a receipt that she still has that specifically says **no refunds** that’s why we let people take samples so they make sure they take the correct floor for their home. As many people here know that this is a family and USMC veteran owned and operated store and we treat people with respect. We have extensive knowledge about flooring and helped her get a floor that was waterproof that they did not want to install. We then proceed calling our supplier which does take returns at a 20% cost. Which they claim we stole but we have to give that to our supplier to return the floor just like any other store that charges restocking fees for special orders. We tried to help them and get their money even though we do not take returns and they accepted the 20% from the supplier. We never sold a wrong floor. The customer saw and took a sample and we gave her that exact floor that all the names and numbers match to the sample to the receipt and to all the boxes they took. We never sold a wrong floor. We’re just following store policies that she was well aware of when she signed and payed for her floor.

name: Stephen Moore
text:
Hands down the best and most helpful hardware store on the Eastern Shore. The folks there are actually so helpful I drive there pretty much every weekend from Mobile for something.

It’s refreshing to have a place you can go where folks take time to actually help you. My go 2 guy there is Ridge. I have never had a single project he did not direct me in the right direction and tried to find the most cost effective option.

I give these guys my highest recommendation
5 ⭐️ Plus

resp.text: Thank you for your support, Stephen!  Appreciate the review!

name: Larry Barnette
text:
I'm in there a LOT. Their fastener section is better than the big chain stores.
The only complaint I have is the guy at the register that asked me why I was wearing a mask, and I told him that I was in heart failure (I should have told him to mind his damn business) he then told me me that he had TWO heart transplants and his cardiologist told him NOT to wear a mask, as if to belittle me.
I'm not calling him a liar, but my Cardiologist sure wants to meet his doctor.

name: Jack Minto
text: Stopped by Home Hardware in Daphne Sat but they were closed and walking out of the door to go home.   I started to leave but Amanda stopped me and asked what I was needing.  I told her and she said she would help me.  What a great experience I had there and I thank them for going above and beyond.  We are lucky to have them in Daphne.

resp.text: We're so glad to help you out, Jack!  We're happy to be in Daphne!

name: Derrick Crane
text: The hours on Google state they are open at 7 am on Saturdays.  At 7:06 the lights were off and the parking lot was empty.  They've been open before at 7 am as I've been there.  Come 11 am I called and couldn't get anyone to answer a phone.   A friend of mines business had a delivery scheduled from them today as well, and nobody showed up.  I like dealing with small locally owned businesses, but the big box store got the money today simply for being open during their stated hours.  This place seems to have gone downhill since changing ownership.

resp.text: Hi Derrick, thank you for sharing your experience.  We've shared them with the senior managers to review.  If you would like someone to reach out directly, please feel free to fill out a form on our website: https://www.homehardwarecenter.com/Contact-Us

name: Daniel Bostick
text: The most awful unfriendly downright wretched place I have ever attempted to do business with..  I even went back and tried 3 times thinking the first two may have just been bad days for the beyond homely slightly female in some characteristics, although too difficult to say for sure whether it was a man, woman, or some evil physical manifestation of a succubus.  I can not understand for the life of me how they are still in business.  Must be a sham front store for something else or they have too my foolish pride to consider closing the doors even if it would be step one by any professional who reviewed their service standards for 15 seconds.   Oh and the prices are Beyond ridiculous!  Do yourself a favor and keep driving for 10 minutes until you hit home depot and lowes.  Only in this case would i recommend those big box stores over something local, but this case is far beyond extreme!

name: Allen catdaddy V
text:
Absolutely terrible customer service. I called 11/20/19 to get a lumber package delivered to save some time. I knew it would be a bit more expensive but more convenient. Delivery was quick and early 11/21/19 unfortunately delivery is at wrong address 100 yards from where it should be and about 15 boards were incorrect. Still no biggie just let them know and I would think it would be taken care of. First call was 8:40 am. Left a message for Dino with another salesman and on his cell phone. Second call was about 12:30 pm, third call was at 3:00 I was told he was still with a customer. I asked the person on the phone to please tell him so that I could hear him answer I needed a call back today, and he did. 3:30 pm Dino calls I explain 15 boards were to be pressure treated and the delivery was in the wrong spot (address) I was then argued with that I didn’t order pressure treated I wrote down the prices quoted and if it wasn’t p.t it was expensive white wood. He put me on hold when he came back to the phone he said the contractor that came in and paid told him the location. I explained it was all done over the phone and there was only me. Where he described is exactly where I told him to put it. Unfortunately that’s not where it was put. He said he would call me back and get it straightened out. No call back, so 11/22/19 I called and left a message with a nice young lady for the sales manager.(I was told his name is Jason).No call back!! I go to see if the package has been moved that afternoon. I have pressure treated wood but package not moved. So much for convenience. Now I will have to pay someone to move the wood. Oh yeah still no call back or invoice. Never again!!

Update, still no call. 11/27/19

resp.text: The pictures of the delivery show the load to be at the end of the gravel driveway by the barn and the exact material delivered that was paid for on the ticket.  I'll find out more info on Monday and be in touch.

name: Joe Crowhurst
text: 53 Hardware is the country feed and seed store I remember growing up out west.  The difference is that 53 Hardware seems to have brilliant insight into the average need of an average homeowner.  Nearly every time I decide to check 53 Hardware before "going to town", I am elated to find the thing I need - with options for price point and brand occasionally.  Truly, 53 HW saves me money and time.  Many home projects where I discover, elbow deep in it, I am missing one little fastener or that one piece to get done, 53 HW comes through.   Hey, they mix paint as well!  Good stuff to boot.  Recently they mixed a color for me that did not come out right. They took my number as they were closing.  The next day I received a call from the owner to let me know they figured it out and it was ready for pickup.  That kind of service with excellent price point and products is what you get from this store l.  Overall, 53 Hardware saves me a lot of time, frustration, and money.  That is well worth my short drive to 53 Hardware for that "one thing" at a good price, if not better than the big box.  If I know they have what I need, 53 Hardware is my primary place to shop for home DIY and other garden needs.  I highly recommend a trip to 53 Hardware for your DIY home and garden needs.

name: Kevin Cosma
text:
If you're a big company and want to do business with V & W, then you'll probably get treated right.

But, from my personal experience as an individual, they couldn't care less about you.
They did not have the part in stock, and they had no interest in trying to obtain it for me. (even though they said they order it if I couldn't get it anywhere else)

I've never been to a business that turns away a customer like this.

So, I can take a hint, I will not be back!

resp.text:
Hello Kevin,

We were very sorry to hear about your experience while visiting our business.

As a small locally owned and operated business, we work hard to be a part of the community and to be counted on.  We assure you we care very much about your plumbing needs.

Please contact me at the Birmingham location 205.324.9521, I would be happy to personally help you with the part you need.

- Lee Herritt, Owner

name: Dana Hamilton
text: Lauren Doss of V&W Supply Company was tremendously helpful to my husband and me recently when we remodeled both of our bathrooms.  V&W has a large selection of bathroom and kitchen fixtures, ranging in style from traditional to ultra-modern.  Lauren met with us and walked us through their large showroom,  demonstrating features of the various products, helping us to chose products that would fit our needs and budget.  After we had made our selections, she coordinated the delivery with our contractor, and the delivery arrived perfectly on schedule.  All of the products are high quality at an affordable price.  We highly recommend V&W Supply Company for bathroom and kitchen fixtures and plumbing needs.

resp.text: Dana thank you so much! We would love for you to post photos of your remodel! Call us if you need anything.

name: Bridget Smith
text: I stopped by to see a Kohler faucet in person, I was told I needed an appointment. The faucet I came to look at was literally 15 feet from me, the front desk guy chuckled when I asked if I could just look at that one faucet and be on my way, he shook his head while exaggerating a nooooooo. I would have called back and placed the order with their sales person but went a mile down the road to Southern Pipe & Supply and purchased the faucet. Work on your customer service.

resp.text:
Dear Ms. Smith,

First off we are sorry you experienced frustration while visiting our showroom.

Since March 25, 2020 for the safety of our customers and our employees we have enforced a strict policy regarding the National Pandemic we are experiencing.

Our policy states our showroom is open by appointment only and there are exactly 3 signage points before entering our showroom to explain this policy.

In reading our previous reviews you will see we provide not only a high quality product, but a fantastic customer experience.

We would like to encourage and invite you to make an appointment so you can experience this service for yourself.

Thank you for visiting our store.

name: Romina Foster
text: Awful customer service. First of all, it took them forever to get the shipment for our order. When the plumber came to install everything there was a piece missing. I called about it on Friday and said they would call me back. They never did, so I had to call again on Monday. The lady who sold us the items (Dawn) was very curt, saying that she had put that piece in the box herself and she could order another one, but she would have to charge me for it. I did not appreciate the way she talked to me or the way she handled the situation. She made it sound like I was lying about the missing piece. I told her to not order another one, that I found it on amazon and would get it from there. Thank you very much (not). Never ordering from there again, especially from Dawn!

resp.text:
Ms. Foster, we were sorry to hear of your disappointment. As you can see from our many great reviews, customer satisfaction is one of our primary goals.

When you left your first message on Friday our customer service representative was off that day. She did return your call first thing Monday morning and when you told her that the escutcheon was missing from the order she did check and didn’t find that anything was left behind.

Dawn was very apologetic if she sounded curt with you and she did mention she called and left a message to apologize.

Dawn managed to find a replacement piece for you and your mother-in-law came and picked it up yesterday.

Once again we are sorry for the frustration, the miscommunication, and inconvenience this may have caused you.

Please do not hesitate to give us a call if there is anything else we can do for you (205) 324-9521.

name: Silvery Nova
text: The first problem is the delivery service company that Home Depot uses for direct deliveries,Central Transport. My 1st initial delivery date changed three time before it was actually attempted to be delivered on March 3rd. On March 3rd the shipment came on a long bed truck with a pallet dolly. My shipment is a pallet of 33 boxes of porcelain tile., plus 7 additional boxes they put on the same pallet. The right side of the pallet was coming apart due to the immense weight of the tile . The driver could not move the pallet down the truck. He was not going to be able to pull it up the small slope on my driveway. What on earth were they even thinking?They needed a fork lift. I called Home Depot and they got the Transport company on the line while I was on hold. I ended up being told the transport company needed to take care of this and they would contact me in 24 to 48 hours. Which they never did. I had to call them. On 3/5 Friday I called central transport and they told me the shipment would be delivered on Monday between 11 and 12. They never showed. I checked the shipment tracking and found that they changed it to Tuesday 3/9! I got no call, text, or phone call.So Tuesday 3/9 I message them to find out eta. They said the drivers hadn't left yet and to keep checking they will update me. That never happened. So I wait and wait and I get a call from Home Depot letting me know the tile has arrived at THE STORE. I was never told anything about this.They will be delivering the tile on Monday 3/15....

Which I corrected him and pointed out and literally touched again the same appliances that I wanted. Apparently some way some how after all this confusion. They magically had sold out. So my thinking leads me to believe the person I spoke to on the phone didn't bother to check or maybe something with system either way wasted my time and here's the kicker the way the guy tried to put it was like I could go to another home depot after I already paid. name: Robyn Curry
text:
**EDIT**
Since the freezer mishap below the management staff (namely Dave) has gone above and beyond to make things right by me. I feel like The Home Depot has redeemed themselves and they have earned my business once again.

I ordered an upright freezer to be delivered to my home. I missed three days of work for no-show deliveries and countless hours on the phone trying to get a freezer delivered and all I got in return was excuses and finger pointing. I had three managers from the West Mobile location involved in this situation (Dave, Cameron, and Jonathan) as well as the customer service help line. They were all aware of the fiasco that had occurred with this delivery yet when I asked what could be done no solution was offered. After a month of no freezer from the Home Depot I cancelled the order and bought one from Lowe’s. I had it the very next day. The Home Depot was always my go-to home improvement store but in light of the lack of customer service in this particular situation I think I’ll reconsider that.

name: Shaun Steffensen
text:
If you order appliances from somewhere, do yourself a favor and not order from Home Depot. First, the people who are selling the appliances do not know much about them. I was told that for installation of my microwave, I needed an outlet in the wall that it was being installed on. Great. I'm good. WRONG!!! The outlet had to be above the microwave.... Something that would have been nice to know, but they could not communicate that properly.
Then, the delivery/installation people had no idea what they were doing. They were more of a delivery company, not an installation professional. They could not install my gas range. They damaged my microwave. So, really, they weren't even a good delivery company. Home Depot just subs out delivery to the cheapest company....and you can see the quality when your damaged items arrive!
And I pray for you if you have ANY problems with your delivery or installation!!!
Count on a couple of things: 1) You will spend hours on the phone getting to talk to the right person. Once you think that you have the right person, they will tell you they have to check on something and they will have to call you back. OR, the right person is "on lunch" and they will call you back. After giving them ample time for "lunch" (3 hours) when you call them back, you will be told that they were "off today" but they will return your call in the morning.
Basically, it's a game of ping-pong and it takes days to get simple questions answered because, obviously, no one who works there wants to actually do anything.
I can't believe I dropped over $7K in there and they can't even answer a simple question!!!!
Buyer beware!!! Shop at Lowe's!!!

text: I ordered $1,600 worth of appliances on black Friday to furnish my investment property. I scheduled them to be delivered on Friday, 12/22, and I was told the delivery time frame would be from 2pm-6pm. I planned accordingly and the my appliances were never delivered! No CALL or anything. It took me 4 different phone calls to reach an actual person. The delivery people could not be reached. I waited at the property until 10pm. I went to the store the next day and spoke with the manager, and apparently I was the 3rd customer complaining of no delivery and no notification. The store could not reach the delivery service because they were closed, and would not re-open again until that Tuesday after Christmas. I was told they "might" start calling customers then to attempt to re-schedule deliveries. I found this to be completely unprofessional and unacceptable. I cancelled my order and was refunded my money. I am showing my rental Wednesday and it will be empty. Home Depot has hurt my business.

text: We bought our washer/dryer a couple of years ago from them and have loved it. We had an issue with our washer leaking and called another local repair service who came out and charged us $140 to look around and say they couldn’t fix it. We called Sears Hometown Repair in Foley and they quickly sent out Daniel who opened the washing machine and said it was a simple fix with the hose!! I told him about the other repair company and he was gracious enough to track down the part we needed and come out the following day and fix it!!! He only charged us $100 for the part AND labor for both days!!! Can’t brag on him enough as well as this store. They are honest, efficient and very professional. Thank y’all again!

name: Kristin Willis
text: I ordered a washer online and picked it up on a Thursday. Once we got it home and took it out of the box we noticed that the front of it was caved in. We called Sears and they told us to bring it back up there. They wouldn't do any kind of scratch and dent discount or I would have took it right back home. Instead they ordered another one and said it would be there the following Tuesday & that they would deliver it for free. Come Tuesday still no washer in and they said they would call me back to let me know when it was supposed to be in and I never received a call. That next Monday I finally received a call that my washer was in but couldn't be delivered until the following day. I ended up going and picking it up bc I was tired of having to wash my clothes in the sink. I will never get anything from there again!!!

name: joey walker
text:
For the managers of this store.... please tell me what quota you must meet before you get to go home? What legally set hours must you follow to achieve said quota? When you are holding up a delivery driver for 30+ minutes BEFORE even answering the door.... you loose us money, make it nearly impossible to get home, and push back all further deliveries.

A driver unlike a store employee (store employee has set hours by their employer) a driver has legal hours we must follow for the safe operation of the vehicles we drive. Our employer makes a set quota of loads/ stops before we can park for the night and go home. Anything that goes wrong with that quota drops everything about that day!

Think of that next time you decide to leave a driver at the back door unanswered!!!

text: Management at this location unfortunately provided the worst customer service I’ve ever experienced. The representative on the phone couldn’t believe we were being treated in such a manner. I spent an hour and a half patiently trying to get help while two managers continuously walked away in the middle of a conversation, after turning around and forcing me to talk to their backs, while the third said she was going home and was no longer interested in helping. One also referred to me as “this” to another employee before storming off. I might have understood management’s disrespectfulness and laziness if I had been unpleasant but that certainly wasn’t the case. I highly recommend visiting another location, or another store altogether, if kind customer service is needed.

name: nsanejain
text: First of all, I am disabled and no one would want to live in my body even for an hour. When I arrived, fresh from having an MRI which made me hurt even worse from laying flat, I saw a ride along cart and got on it. I was having a very hard time walking. The cart was over half charged but the only one on that side. (Of course plenty were left out in the parking lot, guess I should have gotten one of those.) Anyway, as I'm starting to go, a greeter tells me, ma'am, that was is being charged, and needs to continue charging. Made me feel like I couldn't use it. So I took it back, and hobbled to shop best I could. I couldn't get everything I needed, because the pain was excruciating. She did not offer to find me one, either. The more I hobbled around, the more it irritated me. I should have gotten her name and contacted corporate. I know who to contact as I used to work for Wal-Mart before I became fully disabled. I am so disabled, I had a "tough judge" and they concluded that I couldn't work ANY job. But this lady made me feel as if I couldn't use the cart which was well over half charged. I know she was a medium complicated, a bit heavy set and wore glasses. I will still contact corporate over this. I had a helper with me, but couldn't stay in the store long enough to finish shopping. My helper had to just take my groceries to checkout for me as I hobbled back to my handicapped parking spot to wait in the passenger side. It's already bad enough that the store was out of a lot of stuff, but the thing I am really upset about was being treated like I didn't need the cart. Next time I will be quite rude instead of my usual nice personality. That lady should be put in the backroom on cap 2 where she belongs. A greeter, who is part of AP, should be very nice and accommodating. When I worked at Wal-Mart I always went above and beyond for customers. Customers are who buys the things that pay employees. If I didn't live 40 minutes away from a Wal-Mart I would go back and get her name. I do plan to, but will go ahead tomorrow and contact corporate. I will not go back to whittlesey rd Wal-Mart ever again, except to get her name. None of my family, nor myself will ever shop there again. Do better, and don't treat people less than, it will only lead to write ups and dismissal. Very dissappointed and hurt honestly. Wish that lady had to live in my body for a whole week. She would be crying in pain every day and see why she should treat people better. And anyone reading this, when you are treated badly at any Wal-Mart, go and complain to CORPORATE. The managers may not do anything, but corporate takes things like this seriously. And know that the Wal-Mart employees make at least $13 an hour now. They should be doing MUCH better. Blessings to the good people still out there.

name: Laura Standard
text: The aisles are constantly blocked with personal shoppers and their carts as well as stock carts and stock personnel.  Often the personnel are standing around talking so you have aisles blocked by equipment and employees who show complete indifference to customers trying to navigate the aisles.  Or, all the carts seemingly abandoned blocking the aisles and no personnel to be found.  There are nasty spills on the floors causing slippery surfaces and gumming up customers shoes.  Only two produce dispensers had any plastic bags available in the produce department.  Then there are long lines at the full service check out as well as self service because there’s not enough of either.  And once again, employees at the front of the store standing around talking to each other or sneaking a look at their phone.   All of this, mid afternoon on a Friday,  not after a super bowl Sunday blow out or ice- snow-sleet panic buying in the south...Add to that shopping environment rude customers who do not follow minimum etiquette guidelines and you have the big box supermarket from the other side of darkness.  I won’t be back.

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️💫  For Renea that took my call Today 12-9-20 at 12:50pm at  Walmart on Whittlesey  Blvd, Columbus, Ga 31909. I needed blood work done at Quest Diagnostic. I accidentally left my drivers license inside Quest and did not notice until a little over an hour and 40 miles later and 10 minutes before Quest closed for lunch and I was Frantic 🤯 wanting to be sure that they were there and I didn’t drop them somewhere unfortunately the only number I could find was automated only I was really starting to Panic my husband told me to call the Walmart I’m thinking it’s the Christmas season the store was packed and I don’t believe Quest is an actual part of Walmart but with time ticking and me panicking (I am from NYC with a NYC drivers license that cost about $100 to replace and a flight back to NYC in a few days) on the verge of crying  there was a voice of an Angel on the other end she said” Hello Thank You for Calling Walmart this Renea How may i help you?” I explained to Renea my situation and before I could finish she ask if I would hold on that she would go right away before they closed for lunch  and she returned with the amazing news that she had my licenses Renea went above and beyond for me If everyone working in customer service was like Renea it would be an amazing, and all would be right in my world ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
.

text: Ahhhh Wal Mart-what can I say that hasn’t already been said? The employees present in the store may or may not be of assistance and  may or may not know where items can be found. The only checkout lanes open late at night are the self checkout lanes-however this allows for a fairly smooth checkout experience. Positive-the only 24 hour grocery and market in town, when the family is sick with the flu and some emergency Theraflu, paper towels and soda is needed, I know I can find it here. That being said-what’s up with the guy in the leopard skin cape running up and down the aisles, the emaciated gentleman pulling an equally emaciated chihuahua (dog dressed as Santa!) in a red wagon through the aisles? One wonders if this store should employ it’s own security (like Target, or Dirt Cheap, or any of the local markets). But it’s a free country I suppose.

They made no attempt to make it easier for you to get around the store and in fact seemed put off when you tried to go around them. The foul language was something that I was surprised to hear no attempt to keep it low in fact at one point they were shouting the f-word at each other. Also in the meat department you think they were having a big party. There were four  or five employees gathered and they were really yucking it up. Four female employees we're walking side by side down an isle and made no attempt to move so I could get by in fact I had to stop my cart and wait for them to pass. I suppose at some point you just have to give up and figure, where else could they get a job, Walmart will hire anyting.

I give this particular Walmart a 3 out of 5. This place has an inventory problem. Whatever you are looking for this Walmart is most likely to be out of it. And I will give this Walmart the benefit of the doubt, that maybe demand is so high that they can’t keep up with supply. But any manager can figure out forecasting. Even when you walk through the isles you will see many empty selves all over the store.
This Walmart naturally gets busy and they don’t have enough cashiers. It’s faster to go through the self checkout, but I want to be able to support the working man/women and not use technology that replaces employees. But this Walmart just doesn’t have the man power for my patience.

name: Lauren
text:
**Update: Surprise! Surprise! I have another bad review for this horrible store. I am beyond irate at this point. I have been getting my prescriptions filled here for years and over the last year it has been a nightmare. Today, I called the pharmacy to get my prescriptions filled, and asked if there were 90 day supplies available by my doctor. She placed me on hold for over 10 minutes, and NEVER CAME BACK. I hung up and called right back, and the pharmacy was CLOSED for lunch. From my previous experience at this pharmacy, I would bet that this was done to me intentionally. EVERY time I go there to pick up prescriptions, the employees are beyond rude, and treat me like I don’t deserve to be served there. These kids are playing with people’s health. The ONLY reason I get my medications filled at Walmart is because I can actually afford them there. I am so angry and disappointed at this situation, but also because I KNOW nothing will change at Walmart. I attempted contacting management today, and they couldn’t even bother to pick up the phone to talk to me. I have also complained to the corporate website to no avail. 🙄🤷🏻‍♀️ WHEN WILL I LEARN? 😩

**update: On 5/20/18 I walked by the fish area and the beta fish CUPS were stacked on top of each other!!!!! I spoke to the manager and informed him the fish could suffocate and die because of this ignorance. I urged him to PROPERLY TRAIN his employees or to stop selling fish. I was so disgusted I couldn’t even shop there. I do have photo proof, but google won’t let me post a picture.

Most employees are rude and have no idea how to answer most questions. Occasionally I’ll run into a friendly employee. My biggest concern is the state of their fish. Walmart should NOT be selling live animals, especially if their employees have no real training on how to care for living creatures.

text: This is the rudest, most unprofessional store I have ever been to!!! It was a gift and I said maybe it was purchased online. She said sorry but if it did not come directly from that store I could not get credit or swap it or something else. I called customer service and they confirmed I could swap or get credit at any store as long as it was purchased from Walmart so with the same lady and she said the same thing sorry that's our rule! Maybe someone from another location in Columbus like Blackmon Road could show them how customer service should be!!!! This is ridiculous and not acceptable. On another occasion I went to the deli to purchase some meat and cheese and and was told that they were in the process of cleaning the slicer and an it would be at least 2 hours this was on a Friday at 5. name: C. Brown
text:
7/22/2016
I absolutely HATED this location because the setup seems backwards and confusing to me. It seems cluttered and discombobulated. Nothing is organized or convenient, which is why I NEVER shop here.

However, I placed an online order which had to be picked up there so I had no choice but to go there yesterday. I was so shocked at the service I received, I had to do a double take at the banner store name.

Walk in the store and head straight to the pick up section. No sooner than I hit the service screen, a woman pops up, greets me and asked if I've been helped, excuses herself and walks to the back. Before the door could shut, Jenn walks out the other door behind the register and greets me with a friendly salutation and asks, "How may I assist you today?" I'm thinking, "Am I actually at Walmart?" I tell her, give her my order number and ID (which she politely requested), she finds the info on her screen, and before walking to the back asks, "Would you like some water while you wait?" As she reaches behind her.

WAIT, WHAT? Did she just offer me water? I decline, she excuses herself to fetch my package and I look behind the counter to see a small fridge. SHE DID offer me water... I had to check the sign to remind myself that I was at Walmart and not some fancy schmancy store.

She brings the order out, confirms it, does whatever she has to while making small talk, I sign for it and I'm out...took less than 7 minutes.

Still in a daze, I walk to Electronics to find the Apple TV thing. Walking through I don't see it. Spot a guy working on something and ask him (Robert, is his name, I think). He quickly, without hesitation, stops whatever he was doing and promptly unlocks a cabinet, all the while greeting me and informing me about the item I've requested.

So now I'm really paranoid, cause he has actual KNOWLEDGE of the item...this has got to be the TWILIGHT ZONE! He rings it up along with my other stuff while chatting away. Everything done, he thanks me for shopping at Walmart (really) and I'm out!

I still don't like this location and wouldn't go back unless by force, but this was a great experience for which I HAD TO write about.

text:
For the 3rd time in six weeks when I went to the Walmart on Whittlesey to pick up my groceries they were not ready when promised. On two occasions I had to wait until the next day. Today my groceries were to be ready by 9am. I knew they were running behind so I arrived at 11am. I sat in my car with my 8 year old daughter for over an hour before I could get an employee to talk to me and no on would answer my phone. By the time my groceries were brought to my car it was 1:05 pm AND my car battery had died. When I told the Walmart employee that my car battery had died because I had waited so long I received a blank stare and he walked away. Thanks to the kindness of strangers who were also being held hostage waiting for their groceries I was able to get jumped off and on my way after sitting in your parking lot for almost 2 1/2 hours. My advise to you is to communicate clearly and quickly with your customers. Making them wait for over an hour before you even acknowledge them is unacceptable. You had my money and you had my groceries so what choice do I have other than to wait when no one will communicate to me when I should expect my groceries.
I have been a loyal Walmart grocery online customer since the program started in my area last October, check your records. I use this program because I am a working mother of 3 and this allows me to spend more time with my family and less time walking up and down aisle of the grocery store. Well on three occasions now I have waited an hour or more... I could have done the shopping myself. Needless to say I'm done. I was a loyal Winn Dixie customer before online grocery and since it is no longer a reliable, time- saving service I will be headed back to Winn Dixie. I was nice while it lasted but if you continue to conduct business in this manner you will lose more customers than just me.
Best of luck!

text: Don't ever take your vehicle to the automotive dept at the wal mart on whittlesey they are not helpful nor are they knowledgeable of their products I called to ask about battery for my truck the sales associate i spoke with said they had a battery in stock that could fit my truck so I called around to other places to get more prices however I eventually called wal mart back bc they had the best price Lori answered the phone I asked her again about the battery and she also told the battery would fit my vehicle I also asked her could they install the battery she said yes I told her I'm on my way I got there at 6 to purchase the battery and have it installed only to be told they could not install it today I would have to come back the next day I told Lori I wish I would have known that I wouldn't have come today so I waited the next day I got there around 815 and was told it would be a 2 hour wait for my battery to be installed so I left my truck there to only be called 3 hours later from a sales associate saying the battery does not fit my truck!!!!!! I was so livid!!! So I returned to wal mart to get a refund and take my services else where I asked the other associate about the battery to only be told it must have been a new person who told me the battery would fit my truck and if was her or lori they knew better I then told her Lori is the one who sold me the battery !!!!! They then took forever to return my money due to no money being in the register then they left the battery that couldn't fit inside my truck !!!!!!!! Needless to say I will never return to this wal mart automotive department for anything again their customer service is horrible !!!!!

text: Some of these employees are SOOOOOOO RUDE! My partner was at the coinstar machine & it took his coins without giving an accurate count. There was a customer service center employee by the name of Virginia Love that came to his aide because she saw it happen too. I walked up as they were on the phone with coinstar customer service, but what blew me was the fact that an employee by the name of VONICE was tasked with helping them solve this issue and she had a horrible attitude about it. She wasn't looking us in the face at all, and when we asked her questions, she'd mumble something and walk away. She wasn't giving us direct answers AT ALL, and she was getting upset with my partner as if it was his fault the machine malfunctioned. She was speaking to Miss Virginia Love SO disrespectfully. it was disgusting how bad her attitude was, ESPECIALLY with how rude she was being to Miss Love, who is visibly older than her. Everyone knows not to disrespect your elders. Miss Love was only trying to help my parter so they would know he wasn't lying. I understand that there is only so much they can do with the coinstar machine without a coinstar vendor present, but VONICE had an attitude from the start. There was another very round woman that came to unlock the machine, she had an attitude as well, but her name tag was flipped over so I couldn't see it. She called my partner "shawty," as if that was professional. she said "scu'me shawty" WHAT? Why is that your preferred choice of communication when interacting with customers? The whole experience was mind blowing. However, I am very appreciative of Miss Virginia Love for all of her support, considering how rude the other employees were. It's quite obvious that Miss Love should've been in a higher position as opposed to VONICE who clearly needs more training. Someone needs to address this.

text: They are well stocked and clean. The staff could be more friendly and helpful. They have the best prices in the area so they get a good amount of business through there. The parking lot is well lit and it's a safe place to shop.

text: There are always a lot of people when I go. But the employees that work there are always so nice and helpful.

name: Katie Rhoads
text: As far as the store in general goes it’s just like every other Walmart. A young lady that works there, her name is Rebel, is awesome! I had some issues with paint that was mixed by a different worker (this was the 2nd can I had mixed, after she mixed my first original can that I painted with). The 2nd can didn’t match the first after I painted and it dried. I don’t believe they had it on the correct setting with they mixed it.  I found Rebel in the store the next day and she fixed me a new can and it matches perfect! It’s nice to find an employee that knows what they are doing and is super friendly! Give that girl a raise!

text: They don't have food on the shelves or in the freezer. They are too busy working about the people on line. But there are a lot of people who like to shop for themselves. No enough cashiers. name: Donna Donna
text:
I was handed a coupon for free batteries at self check out. My husband immediately went to use it , and was told it "didn't work". What the hell Walmart?

Half the people in here wear no masks, not enforced AT ALL. 1/4 not covering their nose , WHICH IS PART OF RESPIRATORY SYSTEM. The other 1/4 are masked. I will stay out of here.  I am including employees.
I think Wal-Mart cleans shopping carts.

Courteous employees for the most part. Stocked better than some.
Dressing rooms are closed. The store closes at 6pm so get there early.

text: Clean, organized, wish there were more registers open, but everything moved along smoothly

name: Mel Bice
text: Sad place know one can set up phone they said me ,in ny state walmart no problem,need hire proper people!

name: Sheila Wilson
text: I have just about stop going to walmart, because no matter when I go I can not fine what I want, they have either stop carrying it or do not restock once it is out.  Most of the employees are rude and act like they do not want to be there.  I have also found that they there prices have almost doubled since this time last year.  I can fine at grocery stores what I am looking for at a cheaper price or the exact same price.  They wanted $29.00 for a 12 pack of Charmin one day,  needles to say I definitely did not buy it.  They are  Price gouging like crazy.  Like walmart does not have enough.

text: Walmart's curbside shopping is wonderful. The associates are very efficient and do a great job selecting the merchandise that meets our needs. Thanks Walmart!!

name: Michael Sung
text: Standard Walmart with standard items that you find at many other Walmart’s. However, what makes this Walmart different is that it seems everything was very much in order. Unlike some other Walmart’s, this place didn’t look like a disaster and I’m sure it’s because of the staff take care of the store. Kudos to the staff for making this an inviting and comfortable place to shop!

text: Grocery department is always nice and clean and organized.  Stockers are friendly and helpful. Meat department always arranged nice and is clean. name: D.C.J. News Media
text:
This store does a pretty good job of it. Been there several times. Most of the people are friendly and helpful.

I notice from store to store they all have their own flavor. You can call it an attitude of helpfulness and just good manners. Some are far better than others.

This store carries a large selection of firearms compared to others in the chain, in fact I've been to several others across America that have had zero because of state laws, or the local community is far left and anti gun.

This is the explanation I have been given by their employees as to why certain stores were absent of arms.

This may or may not be of concern to anyone specific such as a hunter,or sportsman. VS. someone who is not.

This store is cleaner than some stores in the chain. It's a full size store with the standard offerings.

This store also had a drive through Rx at it's side, which I have only seen a few which I think they all should have for disabled folks.

BTW the management here always seem to do pretty good 😊 by folks that I've seen or experienced. I certainly have not found this to be true at most others in the chain.

text:
Most of the employees in this store are friendly and helpful. There's the occasional poor performer, but that's to be expected with the number of employees they have. Selection is decent, particularly for the size of Andalusia. Prices are what you would expect from Walmart.

Stocking is the problem here. Sometimes the shelves are stocked. Too often they're not. I don't blame the employees. It's got to be a management issue. Maybe there aren't enough people hired to stock the shelves. Or perhaps they're doing other jobs. I end up coming back because there aren't very many options without stopping at 10 different stores, but I feel that a store that actually kept their shelves stocked would put this Walmart in a bind.

name: Heisenberg Parks
text: For as long as I can remember I've always used the Pharmacy in Walmart in Andalusia. Mrs Debbie, the head pharmacist, is an absolute sweetheart. She goes out of her way to help people. However, Walmarts Pharmacy Policies are sickening. They will fill and refill and refill Narcotics. Lortab, Oxy, Narcos, any kind of opiates. No limit, no problem. I use to be able to go in 9-10 times a month with Lortab scripts and get them filled no problem. I have since cleared myself up thanks to my wife and kids. I was put on a Opiate cravings suppressant to stay away from them. Walmart NO LONGER fills any kind of Anti Opiate Dependency medicine. They refuse to fill anything that will get you off of painkillers. I was told by an actual Doctor that They make their money off of Opiates, and any kind of suppressant to help get you off is taking away from them. So they have made a policy on NOT HELPING THOSE IN CRISIS! SORRY! SORRY SORRY SORRY! I will continue spreading this info all the way up the chain. Walmart does not care about you or your problems as long as they get that dollar!

text: My small town hardware store been here longer then I can remember. name: Doug Pike
text:
Seems they finally opened up the Garden Center entrance (limited hours). However there is no register open, so you cannot check out there (reason for one less star).

The folks at the Automation Center in Arab Alabama are very helpful. I've purchased two sets of tires in the past few months (two different vehicles). And they have been accommodating to what I needed. Yesterday I was looking for battery for my lawn mower, and the young man pointed me to where they were located with a smile. He had a positive attitude and willingness to help me. After helping me, I heard his eagerness to help the next gentleman waiting for help. Good Job! We need more service like this!

She was very helpful along with the gentlemen that was taking my bags and putting them in my buggy. He came out after me collecting buggys and took mine also. I thank him and drove away but I believe he came back and collected my husband's electric cart. Our whole experience made our day a little brighter.

text: I was able to find the items I needed and the right sizes.  I asked an associate for assistance and she gladly stopped what she was doing to assist me find what I needed. name: STOKED JL
text: I have to give credit were its due . This wallmart I will gladly give them 5 stars . From the moment I walked in I was greeted at the door . she was friendly and informative. My second experience was with lady at the service desk . she was obviously having a rough morning but she still was extremely nice . I was instantly helped with my transaction and quickly on my way to shopping.  While shopping I observed the cleanliness of the rest of the store and all its facilities. The stock was amazing as well . they had everything I needed and more . when came time for my final check out , there was no line what so ever . I went straight through it was a speedy check out with great friendly service . my over all experience was above and beyond my expectations so I will gladly rate this place with max stars . It is a great family friendly place with amazing helpful workers and I will gladly return next time I need anything.

name: Thoehn (Thoehn)
text:
I avoid this place if I can help it. It is true that they have everything in one place and are usually the cheapest on everything except fresh meats and fruit on occasion, but as most mega corporations are prone to do, they exploit their employees for the sake of their bottom line.

I say this from experience, as I used to work for Walmart. They  refuse to pay a living wage, they never keep enough employees on hand - as I am sure many other reviewers have stated, citing the long checkout lines- and what workers they do have on the clock are overworked to the point of hating their job. At least I know I did.

Now that I am no longer an employee but a customer, I see first-hand just how this devotion to nothing but the bottom line affects the public's perceptions of the store. No one WANTS to go to Walmart; we do it because they've pretty much shut down most competition. Cashiers who are already working as hard as they can get blamed for the long lines and if you need assistance, there are hardly enough employees to go around, so you'll likely get some poor guy or gal who isn't even assigned to the department you're needing help with. This usually means that you will be left less than satisfied.

I will give them credit for implementing self-checkout for convenience's sake, but that also means they have even less incentive to keep the front checkouts amply staffed, so it also comes with drawbacks.

Called at 6 because of no response and the pharmacist told me they hadn't filled one because the request was for chewables and they didn't have that, so I ok'd the pill form. Again told 10 minutes. I showed at 6:30 only to find they didn't have her Medicaid information, so waited another 10 minutes only to find out the doctor hadn't signed the scripts and that they knew this, but I didnt get a phone call, nor did they try to reach the doctor/hospital where it was written. Now I'm told they will call. Waited another 10 minutes only for them to tell me it now has to be filled, so I sat down right in front of them. At 7:10 I got upset and stood in line again. Once I got up there the woman at the counter turned around looking for the scripts only to pull them off of the rack where they had been hanging, who knows how long ago. Then it gets passed for the pharmacist to review and I waited another five minutes because he was nowhere to be found. No customer service and the workers are extremely slow. I'll take prescriptions anywhere but here from now on simply because it will be faster absolutely anywhere in town to drive there and back.

text: I NEVER have a problem with Walmart... they are convenient, they always have what I need. Never any problems. Well it says to use or freeze by 9-8-2019.. so usually that means i need to cook it before that date or freeze it.. last night I got it out of the fridge so that i could cook my family a meal. Some of the meat was nasty and was going to have to be wasted. So instead I cooked something different and took my steaks back to Walmart the next morning.. (this morning 9-7-2019) .. they said I had to have the receipt. I told them it says on the package 100% money-back guarantee. They told me they can't take them back without a receipt no matter what. WHATS THE POINT OF SAYING MONEY-BACK GUARENTEE IF YOU DONT HONOR IT! I just got off work from working 12 hour night shift and had to wait 30 minutes for customer service to open just to be told that. I will be taking this to a higher power. These people didn't even try to help me . They told me to cut off the bad parts.

name: Will Wilson
text: I only go here in "emerencies". I don't know if I'll have space for this story so here's the abbreviated version. I have to say 1st that I have always loved Walmart, in general. Cheap prices and they have everything. I won't get into all of the politics of it. I just loved them. Went here at 11:30 pm to get a pre-workout protein bar. Parked, turned off my SUV, (which has heavily tinted windows) and was looking for my headphones. Guy tries to open my passenger front door. I hop out and he immediately bolts and jumps into another vehicle. So far, nothing here is Walmart's fault. Went in to tell the manager that someone is breaking into cars and to call the police. I'll never forget the manager's response. "You'll have to call them yourself. It happens so often that they don't even come when we call them anymore". So, there are times when one of my kids needs diapers or medicine and everything else is closed so I'll go. And there are times during the day when I need something that costs twice as much every where else I've checked so I'll go. But, I never go alone and it's always super quick. Here's the point. It's a Walmart. Just like every other Walmart. But when the employees aren't even willing to go through the trouble of picking up a phone for criminal acts happening on their property, then I'm never going to feel safe with my family at that store. We all know Walmart has cut way back on security in order to cut rising costs (caused in large part by theft). I'm just one person in, what I am assuming is, a sea people that have actually felt the sting of those cutbacks.

name: Rain Davis
text:
This is a continuation of a problem I had with a deep cycle marine battery from the Talladega walmart. I was sent to sylacauga after waiting 5 and a half hours to have a battery tested and returned. Yeah, I admit it was about 20 minutes after the tire/ auto center was supposed to have closed, but I was told by the Talladega employee that a manager at the customer service counter, in sylacauga, would go back and swap out my battery.

So, I mule in this battery to the customer service desk. The cashier told me the auto dept was closed. I replied that a manager was expecting me. Cashier called the customer service manager up, I explained things to her. She said id have to come back tomorrow as well cause they lock up their batteries at night. I asked if anyone in the building had keys. Frustrated she had to do her job, she hops on the phone. Just a few minutes later she yelled across the customer service area, and said I had to follow her.

So I tried, she made sure that she was a good 20' in front of me so she could talk with her coworker without being overheard. Im a disabled veteran. I have to pick and choose when I can hurry, and after hauling this heavy battery around for the better part of a day, I was all out of get up and go. And I especially don't care for your small town, holyer- than- thou attitude cause you "have to turn a key". It's called doing your job.

Anyways, so I make my way back to the battery area. The manager there went on to state several reasons he couldn't do the exchange. From me not having a receipt (handed it to him, with the last exchange receipt) to the battery being old (the color coded sticker dates it back to November of 2018), and finally the managers settled on being unable to do the exchange because the computer says it's already been exchanged. That's 100%, I traded the last box of garbage for this one.

I'll be calling corporate after lunchtime today.

Summation: the employees are killing this big box store. Don't visit Talladega or Sylacauga. They are both garbage and could care less about the customer.

name: Cindy Mauldin
text: People with overflowing carts are allowed to go thru self-service cash registers at the Sylacauga, Al Walmart, causing those of us with 20 or less items to have to wait and wait forever. I have witnessed a lot of theft due to this reckless Walmart procedure. There is no way that any Walmart employees can monitor these thiefs, and also assist others who have computer issues at the self-service registers. There is absolutely NO REASON for a customer to have a cart full of one hundred items of clothes and food, to ever be in the self-service lines. There is not space to accommodate so many items. There must be a limit of NO MORE THAN 25 ITEMS AT SELF-SERVICE REGISTERS. ALL OTHERS MUST BE RE-DIRECTED TO CASH REGISTERS WITH WALMART ATTENDANTS. Doing so will reduce Walmart theft, reduce costs to customers caused by theft, and will allow lines at self- service registers to move quickly, which is the purpose for self-service in the first place. I have seen a husband with one cart and his wife with a second cart, with 6-packs of drinks dangling over the top of carts. This practice must be stopped by Wal-Mart. Intentional theft is the only reason people bring overloaded carts to self- service registers. Walmart needs to stop being blind!!!!

text: The only reason I’m even leaving one star is because you cant-leave zero,I purchased a pressure washer and on first use the hose in pressure washer had no pressure due to hole in hose,keep in mind fresh out the box,I take hose back to Harbor Fright and of course they don’t sell just the hose,I explain my situation to the lady and she called her boss,and tells me I have to return the the whole pressure washer in order to get another on,So I go home to get entire unit return to store I get back to store and exchange it,then the cashier says 76.00 I said what why when I am even exchanging and she informs me that I have to get a 2yr warranty to be able to exchange,and I said I don’t want a warranty bottom line they don’t stand behind their stuff,They lost a good customer at no time was I told I would have to pay for a 2 yr warranty in order to exchange until I was checking out.Communication is Key…Shame on y’all Harbor Frieght

name: Benjamin Schaab
text:
I love the pricing on just about everything from saw blades, grinding wheels, drill bits, ratchet straps, hand tools, sockets and wrenches. But not only is the pricing more than reasonable, and often half, if not more than half the price you’d get at a big box store, the quality is still there. It may not be quite top of the line, but for the price itrms definitely worth it. Their line of Chicago
Power tools are also very reasonable, and having owned a corded power drill and a corded power set of metal sheers, I can’t tell the difference in quality between their line and the big name tool manufacturers. As a professional contractor, Harbor Fright saves me money and gets me the tools I need to get the job done.

Say what you will about Harbor Freight tool quality, I swear by them. No, this is not the tool you buy expecting it to last a lifetime, but if you're wanting a spare set of tools to keep in the trunk of your car for emergencies, to take with you camping, or simply want to try your hand at a new project without going in for the big investment, this is the place.

Quality on the tools can be hit and miss, but when you're buying tools at discount prices like this, you can't expect Craftsman level reliability. On the other hand, everything I've ever had that broke there had a warranty which Harbor Freight was happy to honor.

name: Randy Hearn
text:
If you are doing any kind of work with tools, who doesn't know or like HFTs. I have shopped their for years and am also a club member. As stated in other posts most of the staff are helpful and supportive. While you may find a few that seemed pre-occupied when you ask a question, that is not the norm.

However, today lowered my perspective on this store after talking to a store employee over the phone and the manager.

It seems HFT has known for a long time there is an issue with their emailing receipt system. When you purchase something you can have your receipt sent to you by email, just by giving them a phone number. So apparently by opting into the stores emailing me a receipt, I now will get random receipts by people making up phone numbers or the cashier entering the wrong number.

The store manager seemed to take this lightly, however I believe they need to invest in better software and even better theft prevention people.

The receipt I got stated the last 4 numbers of the CC used, and like they said it was not mine. Fine. However, the system should have alerted the cashier that me as being a CLUB Member did not have that CC number related to my account. It should have also detected that my CLUB member name did not match the name of the person on that CC.

Bottom line we can not get a good grip on crime in our communities if the stores are not going be responsible with our personal information. What may seem minuscule to some can in fact be a huge issue. Did someone just use my phone number to commit a crime? Purchase items fraudulently at their store?

The first person I talked to was frustrated at me, telling me it happens all of the time and is no big deal? Really? I get an email purchase notification and I have to stop what I am doing to make sure someone has not stolen my CC number and used it? Its not a dig deal to them, to the consumers it is a HUGE deal.

So again, it is the consumers responsibility to correct these actions. I was told in order to correct this I must go into the store and request my number be removed from their automatic system. Hmm.... Northern Tools is just down the road guys. Think about it.

If it were not for the issue with the point-of-sale systems, I would give the store a 5 star rating.. You need to address this issue, stop making the consumers do your work for you.

The receipt I got stated the last 4 numbers of the CC used, and like they said it was not mine. Fine. However, the system should have alerted the cashier that me as being a CLUB Member did not have that CC number related to my account. It should have also detected that my CLUB member name did not match the name of the person on that CC.

Bottom line we can not get a good grip on crime in our communities if the stores are not going be responsible with our personal information. What may seem minuscule to some can in fact be a huge issue. Did someone just use my phone number to commit a crime? Purchase items fraudulently at their store?

The first person I talked to was frustrated at me, telling me it happens all of the time and is no big deal? Really? I get an email purchase notification and I have to stop what I am doing to make sure someone has not stolen my CC number and used it? Its not a dig deal to them, to the consumers it is a HUGE deal.

So again, it is the consumers responsibility to correct these actions. I was told in order to correct this I must go into the store and request my number be removed from their automatic system. Hmm.... Northern Tools is just down the road guys. Think about it.

If it were not for the issue with the point-of-sale systems, I would give the store a 5 star rating.. You need to address this issue, stop making the consumers do your work for you.

name: Meesha Telvanni
text: Veggies aren't really fresh or neat. Zucchini  was crammed in so tight you couldn't get any without scraping the others up. Meat area hasn't had a good selection in awhile. Never anyone in the bakery. Many food items on the shelves had no price, and items all mixed up so I didn't know which price was which all through grocery area. A bag of sugar substitute I put in my buggy had a hole in it, got all over my foods and the floor. I asked someone for help so there wouldn't be a mess, and they sighed and said, "what do you want me to just get the bag from you?" So, I went no, I'd like a broom so no one slips on it. Person said they'd get someone. The new person came and was very sweet and cleaned up the mess and asked if I needed a new bag. The cashier didn't ring a lot of my veggies as what they were, even when I told her. For example, I had a ton of poblanos, and she rang them as 3 g peppers. My bag of cherries I weighed at around $8, never made it on my receipt. So somehow they didn't get scanned. Free food not a problem for most, but I buy for several ppl, and need the items on the receipt. So, I gave it a three cause it made shopping from a list very frustrating. I left and went to another store to finish getting what I needed.

name: Ryan Cass
text: This Walmart location used to be my family’s go to for quick shopping but over the years the staff and service have become less helpful. The store is more dirty and disorganized than other locations in the area and there’s several items every other Walmart I go to has but this location always seems to be out of stock so that’s why I had to dock them 3 stars. I’d bump my score up if they would take the time to remodel the store a bit and better train the staff and bump up the inventory.

name: Mary Baldwin
text: This store doesn't appear to be very handicapped/disabled friendly. They have plenty of handicap parking but as far as someone with a disability being able to go in store and shop that's where they apparently have no concern about. If you have/bring your own mobile cart you will be able to shop..however if you don't you may want to use the services of another store because you will be unable to get around the store to shop. I was there tonight and they only had 3 carts in the store. The two on the side which the doors were opened didn't work at all and the third one, which was on the other end of the store on the closed doors side,  wasn't charged nor was it even plugged in to charge the battery.. I asked an employee who was bringing in carts on the closed side if they maybe had a cart outside that hadn't been brought in by chance. He told me he would go get me one and walked away.. After waiting 10 minutes I proceeded to head back to the other side I had originally came in hoping to catch him headed back. Well no such luck he was no where to be seen. Not only that but while I was on my way there I notice two teen girls ( that definitely had nothing wrong and no need to use) playing around the store with each other on two.. Meanwhile the store had myself needing one and gentleman needing one for his wife so we could shop!! I left the store and went elsewhere to do business. The lack of care or concern this store exhibited is not only shamefully sad, disgraceful and angering but it's unethical, incompetent and reprehensible!

text: Visited on my normal Friday evening shopping trip  at around 6:45. I will use the self checkout when I have small amounts so today I got in that line for the self checkout corral. After waiting in line for several minutes and making to that front the young lady says "cards only" I tell her I'm paying in cash and she tells me "I guess you will have to go get in the other lines" and turns away. So we go to one of the self checkout with the belts and when we make it there it too says 'card only'. Next we try customer service but there is a customer having trouble with a return and they turn the lights out on us so we finally go to the tobacco line. Probably should have done that to begin with. So on the way out I call the 1800walmart number to complain her answer was the cash shortage that happened a few months ago or she said "at least that's what they tell me". I'm sure it was someone that has to count down the cash from the self checkout at night decided they wanted to leave early so they pulled all the cash and switched the registers to card only. This has happened on a few occasions at this store. It was once the cleaner and better stocked walmarts but has suffered for the past few years. On the way home my wife and I made the decision to drive the extra mile and start shopping at Target again.

name: Susan DuPre'
text: Grocery Pick-up service.  I shopped online on a Saturday afternoon, scheduled my pick-up for Sunday 12-1 slot, paid online, received online confirmation that my order had been received and would be ready at the time slot I had selected.  On Sunday, I arrived at 12:15 and saw 3 other cars waiting in the designated spots for pick-up.  When I pushed to red button to let the crew know of my arrival, they sounded confused and told me "we'll work it out."  About 10 minutes later, an employee came out to my car and very humbly apologized that my order and the one for the man in the truck next to me had not been noticed, but that they would get the man's order out, then mine would be next, as quickly as they could.  Fifteen minutes after that, the employee pushed the man's order out to his car, unloaded it, and proceeded to have a TWENTY minute discussion with that customer!!!  They were hidden from my view by the man's massive truck, but I could hear them talking - just in regularly toned voices, no yelling or sounds of anyone upset - couldn't hear what they were saying, however.  When the employee finally went back inside the store, it was another 10 minutes before he got my order out to my car!  He again very humbly apologized and blamed the man in the truck for "needing to talk about something".  At this time, I had been waiting almost an HOUR!  I could have gone inside and done my own shopping, then been back out to my car by then!  I was NOT happy, as  it was lunchtime, and my whole family was at home texting me and asking when I would be home with the groceries for lunch!  This service sounds like a convenient option, but in my case, it wasted a lot of my time!  I'm not sure I'll use this service again if I risk having my order overlooked.  I don't have that kind of time!

I responded well not really, he then handed the phone to a little bit older female and in a very huffy voice she ask  NOW WHAT IS IT I CAN HELP YOU WITH? I replied a wire welder, YES WE'VE got them. Ok can you tell me the price of these welders. WELL YOU WILL JUST HAVE TO COME DOWN HERE AND PRICE THEM, DIFFERENT ONES ARE DIFFERENT PRICES. OK can you just give me a price range, that's when she loudly sighed and said SOMEWHERE BETWEEN 150 TO 300. With that attitude i told her I guess I just need to find somewhere else to buy my tools.
